<Seo Canonical="/docs/helpers/enums/heading" Title="Blazorise Heading Enums - Display and Heading Sizes" Description="Heading enums define display and heading sizes for typography. Learn DisplayHeadingSize and HeadingSize values for consistent headings." />

<DocsPageTitle>
    Enums: Heading
</DocsPageTitle>

<DocsPageLead>
    Set heading sizes consistently across your typography.
</DocsPageLead>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    Heading enums keep display headings and regular headings aligned with your design scale without manual CSS.
</DocsPageParagraph>

<DocsPageSubtitle>
    How it works
</DocsPageSubtitle>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    Use <Code>DisplayHeadingSize</Code> for large hero-style headings and <Code>HeadingSize</Code> for standard h1-h6 sizing.
</DocsPageParagraph>

<DocsPageSubtitle>
    Examples
</DocsPageSubtitle>

<UnorderedList>
    <UnorderedListItem><Code>DisplayHeadingSize.Is1</Code> for the largest hero titles.</UnorderedListItem>
    <UnorderedListItem><Code>HeadingSize.Is3</Code> for section-level headings.</UnorderedListItem>
    <UnorderedListItem><Code>HeadingSize.Is6</Code> for small labels or captions.</UnorderedListItem>
</UnorderedList>

<DocsPageSubtitle>
    Reference
</DocsPageSubtitle>

